Cleaner Air, Healthier Cities: The Hidden Benefits of Climate Action

LEVEL 1 — SPATIAL DISTRIBUTION

This histogram shows the distribution of air quality co-benefits across UK administrative regions. Most regions experience moderate benefits, indicating widespread but uneven impacts of climate action.

LEVEL 2 — TEMPORAL DISTRIBUTION

The annual distribution remains relatively consistent over time, suggesting stable air quality benefits from climate action across the study period.
This plot combines cumulative benefits (sum) and temporal trends (slope) to classify regions by benefit level and direction of change, highlighting policy-priority areas.

FINAL (INTEGRASI LEVEL 1 + LEVEL 2)

This plot combines cumulative benefits (sum) and temporal trends (slope) to classify regions by benefit level and direction of change, highlighting policy-priority areas.
Most regions show slow improvement in air quality benefits, while a smaller number experience stagnation or decline.
The gap distribution highlights differences in benefit consistency, with larger gaps indicating more variable air quality improvements over time.
